<p>
<seg id=1> Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat started his first official flight from the Gaza International Airport. </seg>
<seg id=2> The Gaza International Airport was put into operation a day earlier. </seg>
<seg id=3> On Wednesday, Israeli security officials saw Arafat's plane off, which was destined for Paris. </seg>
<seg id=4> Israeli officials are responsible for airport security. </seg>
<seg id=5> The Land for Peace Agreement reached recently by the Israelis and Palestinians has paved the way for the use of the Gaza International Airport. </seg>
<seg id=6> The Palestinians consider the airport as a symbol of their sovereignty and a boost to the Palestinian economy. </seg>
</p>
